meanings.definition: Not able to be understood or explained.
meanings.sent1: The professor's handwriting was so uninterpretable that no one could read it.
meanings.sent2: The ancient text was uninterpretable to the modern scholars.
meanings.sent3: The uninterpretable map led the lost travelers in circles.
meanings.sent4: Her emotions were like an uninterpretable puzzle, confusing everyone around her.
meanings.sent5: The cryptic message left by the spy was intentionally uninterpretable.

meanings.sent1: The strange symbols on the artifact were uninterpretable to the archaeologists.
meanings.sent2: The foreign language was uninterpretable to those who did not speak it.
meanings.sent3: The uninterpretable dance moves left the audience scratching their heads.
meanings.sent4: The silence between them was heavy and uninterpretable, filled with unsaid words.
meanings.sent5: The mysterious code was deliberately made uninterpretable to protect the secret message.
